            "answer_text": "The closest would probably be Persian, if we count languages that are still spoken. It belongs to the same branch as Pashto, but it would have been more similar to Pashto\u2019s ancestor than to the modern language itself. And since Avestan was close to Old Persian, it would be somewhat true that Persian would most likely be the closest language to it. If we talk about languages which are generally considered to be close to Avestan, then it would be Vedic Sanskrit and the Old Persian language, which was used during the Achaemenid empire. Vedic Sanskrit and Avestan are considered sister languages and to be very similar to each other in multiple parts. EASTERN IRANIAN LANGUAGES AVESTAN LANGUAGE I-III Vedic Sanskrit ",
